    <div class="field-name-caption"><block><p>In this Thursday, Aug. 1, 2014 photo, Lee Santamaria, front, of Cooper City, Fla., works with children during a soccer camp held by FC Barcelona in Miami. European clubs like Barcelona, Liverpool and Arsenal have long sent coaches to work at U.S. summer camps, but now some are opening year-round U.S. academies aimed at finding new talent but also to expand their fan bases. This is part of a number of initiatives of major teams to grow their brands in the U.S. (AP Photo/Lynne Sladky)</p></div>    

